Japanese Bought Net 190.6 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-06-01T23:55:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/japanese-bought-net-190-6-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended May 27 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 190.6 billion yen ($2.4 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 26.3 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 54.5 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 162.3 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 287 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 83.2 billion yen in stocks, and sold 40.7 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 163
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  